<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PTM8.1.10">
<l>māvaḷaru meṉṉōkki mātarāḷ māyavaṉaik kaṇṭā ḷeṉṟu</l>
<l>kāvaḷaruṅ kaṭipoḻilcūḻ kaṇṇapurat tammāṉaik kaliyaṉ coṉṉa</l>
<l>pāvaḷarun tamiḻmālai paṉṉiyanū livaiyaintu maintum vallār</l>
<l>pūvaḷaruṅ kaṟpakamcēr poṉṉulakil maṉṉavarāyp pukaḻtak kōrē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Those who master these five-and-five [verses] of the text</l>
<l rend="indent">crafted as a garland	of Tamil, where poetry flourishes,</l>
<l>Composed by Kaliyaṉ about the lord of Kaṇṇapuram,</l>
<l rend="indent">encircled by fragrant groves where gardens flourish,</l>
<l>Saying, “The girl with the soft glance, where darkness flourishes,</l>
<l rend="indent">saw Māyavaṉ,”</l>
<l>Are those worthy of praise as kings of the golden land</l>
<l rend="indent">with the kalpaka tree where blossoms flourish.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
